The req.on is a method in Node.js used to listen for events on a request object. In the context of 
Node.js web servers, req refers to the incoming HTTP request object.
req.on(eventName ,eventHandler )

eventName: A string representing the name of the event you want to listen for. Common events 
include "data", "end", "error", etc.
eventHandler: The function that will be called when the specified event occurs. This function is 
commonly referred to as an event handler or callback function. It usually takes parameters 
specific to the event being handled.






